2	//
3	// Per docs/oracle/05-ai-retrofit-phase-packet.md Phase R7.
4	//
5	// What changed vs the legacy worker:
6	//   - Model calls go through OracleAIClient (R2) via direct provider adapters
7	//     (Vertex / Anthropic / OpenAI raw SDKs — DECISIONS.md D6 / D9) using
8	//     the curated route ID from `settings.default_extraction_route`. R7
9	//     ships the explicit-cache profitability heuristic +
10	//     provider_cached_content lifecycle bookkeeping; native Vertex
11	//     cachedContent lifecycle creation is a round-2 follow-up to R-providers.
12	//   - Output flows through extraction_batches → extraction_candidates →
13	//     extraction_candidate_evidence first. NOTHING writes to permanent
14	//     claims tables before R5's deterministic validator passes.
15	//   - Per-claim quote validation against the matching document_chunk's text
16	//     (not the full document).
17	//   - Per-claim taxonomy validation against active knowledge_top_domains.
18	//   - Race-safe promotion via executePromotion (snapshotInputs path) —
19	//     uses claims.candidate_hash to detect historical duplicates across
20	//     ingestion runs.
21	//   - document_top_domains + document_chunk_top_domains rows written for
22	//     each successfully-promoted claim's domains, so retrieval works at
23	//     the document level even before claims accumulate.
24	//
25	// What stays the same:
26	//   - Download from Supabase Storage via service-role client (private).
27	//   - PDF / XLSX / CSV / text parsing.
28	//   - Chunking + embedding + document_chunks insert (with dedup by hash).
29	//   - Direct + sweep task variants (single document + cron safety net).
